@node FEATURES "Features of Magic Reader"

        · Supports QWK and OMEN formats
        · Supports reply packet editing
        · Supports localization
        · Uses MUI
        · 100% written in assembler
        · Easy to use
@endnode
@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

This version of Magic Reader requires:

        · AmigaOS 3.0 or better
        · MUI 3.8
        · NList.mcc, NListview.mcc, BetterBalance.mcc and ToolBar.mcc (not included)
        · BetterString.mcc (not included) if you are using 020+ version


Recommended:

        · TextEditor.mcc
        · 8MB (!) fast ram
@endnode
@node PROJECT_MENU "Project Menu"

        @{"Open Bundle   " LINK OPEN_BUNDLE}
        @{"Close Bundle  " LINK CLOSE_BUNDLE}
        @{"Import Replies       " LINK IMPORT_REPLIES}
        @{"Settings      " LINK SETTINGS}
        @{"MUI Settings  " LINK MUI_SETTINGS}
        @{"About         " LINK ABOUT}
        @{"About MUI     " LINK ABOUT_MUI_MENU}
        @{"Quit          " LINK QUIT}
@endnode
@node OPEN_BUNDLE "Open Bundle"

A file requester appears allowing you to select a message bundle to be
opened. If you already have a bundle open it will be closed before
opening a new one.

You can also open a bundle by entering it's file name with full path as
a command line parameter when starting Magic Reader.
@endnode
@node CLOSE_BUNDLE "Close Bundle"

Closes bundle. Program warns you before closing if you have new
messages.
@endnode
@node IMPORT_REPLIES "Import Replies"

A file requester appears allowing you to select a reply packet. Magic Reader
opens the packet and merges replies to your bundle if any open allowing you
to re-edit those messages.
@endnode
@node SETTINGS "Settings"

Open settings window allowing you to edit program settings.
@endnode
@node MUI_SETTINGS "MUI Settings"

Open MUI Settings window allowing you to edit MUI related stuff.
Please refer to MUI documentation for further info.
@endnode
@node ABOUT "About"

Displays copyright and version information. If you have a message bundle open
it also displays some information about bundle.
@endnode
@node ABOUT_MUI_MENU "About MUI"

Displays some information about MUI.
@endnode
@node QUIT "Quit"

Exits Magic Reader.
@endnode
@node MESSAGES_MENU "Messages Menu"

        @{"Save Message  " LINK SAVE_MESSAGE_MENU}
        @{"Print Message        " LINK PRINT_MESSAGE_MENU}
        @{"Search        " LINK SEARCH_MENU}
        @{"Add Name to List     " LINK ADD_NAME_MENU}
        @{"Set Bookmark  " LINK SET_BOOKMARK}
        @{"Go to Bookmark       " LINK GOTO_BOOKMARK}
        @{"Steal Tag Lines      " LINK STEAL_TAGS}
@endnode
@node SAVE_MESSAGE_MENU "Save Message"

Saves current message to a file. Message can be saved with or without
the header.
@endnode
@node PRINT_MESSAGE_MENU "Print Message"

Prints current message to printer. Message can be printed with or without
the header.
@endnode
@node SEARCH_MENU "Search"

Allows you to search text.
@endnode
@node ADD_NAME_MENU "Add Name to List"

Adds the name of the current message's author's or addressee's name
to the Name List.
@endnode
@node SET_BOOKMARK "Set Bookmark"

You can bookmark the current message by using this menu. Currently
up to ten messages can be bookmarked.
@endnode
@node GOTO_BOOKMARK "Go to Bookmark"

You can go to bookmarked message by using this menu.
@endnode
@node STEAL_TAGS "Steal Tag Lines"

Allows you to "steal" tag lines from message.
@endnode
@node HISTORY "History of Magic Reader"

Version 0.46 (31. August 1998):
-------------------------------

        - fixed some bugs
        - selectable GUI
        - and something which I can't remember now... :)
        - I have now PPC ;-)

This version was recompiled 16.9 but there is no really any changes...
I think this version has more bugs than previous ones but I tyr to fix
these...


Version 0.37 (31. May 1998):
----------------------------

        - fixed: QWK replies are now packed correctly (major fix)
        - fixed: when using OMEN areas are no longer messed
        - some really small improvements
        - norwegian catalogs are still missing (coming soon)

No PPC yet but I borrowed a Blizzard 1230-IV with 8 meg of RAM.
Not much but better than nothing :)


Version 0.36 (13. May 1998):
----------------------------

        · fixed many bugs
        · again supports 000/010 processors
        · some "documentation" available now...
        · norwegian catalogs also available (thanks to Tom Christensen :)

Please note: this version is released in *hurry* because I sold
my accelerator board and currently I have a plain A1200 :(
So there is no norwegian catalogs in this archive because it isn't
finished yet. Will be available in Aminet on some day..

Also, at this moment I can't create new versions of MagicReader
because I can't compile the code with 2MB of RAM. Development
will be continued when I get PPC board :)


Version 0.33 (25. April 1998):
------------------------------

        · fixed some minor bugs
        · no longer supports 000/010 processors (020 or better needed)


Version 0.31:
-------------

        · archive was distributed with wrong version (0.28) of MagicReader which had lots of bugs
        · now contains fully updated German translation
        · user list implemented
        · some minor bug fixes


Version 0.29:
-------------

        · removed Enforcer hits on exit
        · added internal text editor (requires TextEditor.mcc and Toolbar.mcc)
        · added new features
        · added some graphics
        · added catalogs auf deutsch (Michael Lünse)
        · fixed lots of bugs
@endnode
@node KNOWN_BUGS "Known Bugs"

        · messages on personal area has some text missing... (are still shown correctly
          on their original area)
        · some buttons doesn't work (because feature is not implemented, mostly...)
@endnode
